# Backend — Modular MVC

## Folder layout

```
backend/src/modules/{user|admin}/{module}/
  {module}.routes.js
  {module}.controller.js
  {module}.model.js
  {module}.view.js
```

## Naming

| Layer | File | Export |
|-------|------|--------|
| Routes | `library.routes.js` | `default` Router |
| Controller | `library.controller.js` | `libraryController` |
| Model | `library.model.js` | `libraryModel` |
| View | `library.view.js` | `libraryView` |

- Controller methods: `listSources`, `createSource`, `getSourceById`
- Model methods: `findAllByUserId`, `insert`, `deleteById`
- View methods: `formatSource`, `formatSourceList`
- API prefix: `/api/v1/{user|admin}/{module}/...`
- Route params: `:sourceId`, `:projectId` (camelCase + Id)

## Response shape

```json
{ "success": true, "message": "...", "data": {} }
```

Use `sendSuccess` / `sendError` from `shared/utils/api-response.util.js`.
Use `asyncHandler` for async controllers. Use `req.t('user.library.create.success')` for messages.

## Rules

- User and admin modules never share controllers or models.
- Views convert DB `snake_case` → API `camelCase`; never expose secrets.
- Shared code only in `shared/middleware/` and `shared/utils/`.
